SUMMARY:Wildlife Wonders in Swannanoa
DESCRIPTION:Join Swannanoa Valley WILD! Chapter of NCWF and Friends of Fox Creek Park in Swannanoa as we explore the magnificent world of WILDLIFE including all things plants\, animals\, and ecology. We are currently working on restoration projects at Fox Creek Park and it’s important that we build an understanding of what we’re working to conserve and protect. We’ll learn and ask questions together during this fun and active event! Luke Cannon\, one of Western North Carolina’s premier naturalists and ethnobotonists will be our guide.  \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/wildlife-wonders-in-swannanoa/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/doublebark.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Wildlife Federation
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260407T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260407T163000
DTSTAMP:20260403T221536
CREATED:20260317T174948Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260317T174949Z
UID:10001529-1775575800-1775579400@ncwf.org
SUMMARY:ecoEXPLORE Botany Check-In: Leaf No Doubt! (Columbia)
DESCRIPTION:Join Pocosin Lakes National Wildlife Refuge and North Carolina Wildlife Federation for April’s ecoEXPLORE “Leaf No Doubt” program at the refuge indoor classroom! We will explore our surroundings behind the visitor center while paying special attention to the characteristics of tree leaves all around us to help complete the “Leaf No Doubt” tree challenge! After this program\, your child(ren) will be one step closer to achieving their tree field focus badge! By learning about leaves\, we can make more confident tree identifications which is an important skill. Observing different tree species can tell us so much about a habitat\, surrounding ecosystem\, AND what wildlife species are supported by those trees. \necoEXPLORE is a community science program\, created by the North Carolina Arboretum\, where children of all ages are able to learn how to identify wildlife around them\, help real scientists track wildlife activity\, and earn fun badges and prizes all at the same time! To learn more about ecoEXPLORE\, please visit https://www.ecoexplore.net/
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/ecoexplore-botany-check-in-leaf-no-doubt-columbia/
CATEGORIES:Featured
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Wildlife Federation
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260407T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260407T193000
DTSTAMP:20260403T221536
CREATED:20260306T165155Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T165156Z
UID:10001520-1775583000-1775590200@ncwf.org
SUMMARY:Nature Journaling Workshop (Swannanoa)
DESCRIPTION:Join Swannanoa Valley WILD! Chapter of NCWF in partnership with the Friends of Fox Creek Park as we welcome Carolina Corona for a nature journaling workshop at one of our favorite places in the whole world! Fox Creek Park in Swannanoa. \nReconnecting with the natural world after a disaster can be difficult. We can hold on to fear and even resentment which block our ability to be at peace with nature. Artist Carolina Corona will guide us through various prompts to help us reconnect. Nature Journaling brings us closer to reconnecting and deepening our connection with nature while sharpening our observation and drawing skills. Nature provides us with peace\, beauty\, and infinite wonder. Reflecting in nature by focusing and recording our observations\, thoughts\, and experiences is a practice that can bring healing in times of crisis.  \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/nature-journaling-workshop-swannanoa/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/birdhello.jpg
END:VEVENT
