SUMMARY:Gardening for the Planet (Greensboro)
DESCRIPTION:Join NCWF Triad Wild! Chapter for a joint event with T. Gilbert Pearson Audubon Society at the SAIL Center at the Greensboro Science Center. We will be screening the documentary Gardening for the Planet\, which shows how something as simple as the plants you chose for your garden can be impactful in the struggle to combat climate change. This film will leave you with a sense of hope by showing how even one person can improve the ecosystem in their tiny part of the planet by planting native plants. For those who still want to achieve a landscaped look in their lawn\, the film also demonstrates that this style is still possible while opting for native plants. Join us for an uplifting documentary screening! \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/gardening-for-the-planet-greensboro/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/planet.jpg
END:VEVENT
