SUMMARY:Landscaping for Wildlife with Native Plants (Leland)
DESCRIPTION:Join NCWF in Leland for a presentation by Dr. Rosemarie Pelletier\, Master Gardener and certified landscape designer\, and learn how you can design and build a landscape that supports native plants and wildlife in your backyard. Did you know that oak trees support the caterpillars of over 300 species of moths and butterflies? Did you know a songbird has to feed their chicks 10\,000 caterpillars before they can fledge the nest? Did you know the choices you make in your yard can have an impact on wildlife in the Amazonian basin of Peru? Come learn simple tricks and tips for backyard habitats! All are welcome\, no gardening experience necessary. \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/landscaping-for-wildlife-with-native-plants-leland/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/lelandlandscaping.jpg
END:VEVENT
